<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-05T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/6–546: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">O’Sullivan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-05T17:00:00+07:00">June 5, 1946—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 6—7:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>36. Ho Chi Minh probably will call at AmEmbassy shortly. He has
                            constantly given me impression he would pay great attention to any
                            suggestions made by <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">O’Sullivan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>